1 of each child in this State who has begun the school year under the age of 21 and is found
2 to need special education and related services, whether or not the child is receiving
3 nonduplicative services from another governmental agency.
4 (b) Before these standards are adopted, the State Board shall consult with public
5 and private agencies and persons who are concerned with and knowledgeable about the
6 educational needs of children with disabilities who require special education and related
7 services.
8 (c) The standards for the education of a child with a disability who is enrolled in
9 a school that is operated by an agency other than a local school system may not be lower
10 than the standards for the education of a child with a disability who is enrolled in a school
11 that is operated by a local school system. The standards for the approval of schools located
12 in jurisdictions outside Maryland shall be the same as standards applicable to the approval
13 of schools within Maryland. However, no school located in a jurisdiction outside Maryland
14 shall be approved if the charges for pupils approved by the Department are higher than
15 charges for pupils from any other state for the same services, unless waived by the State
16 Superintendent.
17 (d) The standards shall include:
18 (1) The required qualifications for teachers, administrators, and other
19 professionals serving a child with a disability;
20 (2) Procedures for the identification, evaluation, educational placement,
21 and provision of a free appropriate public education for a child with a disability who
22 requires the provision of special education and related services;
23 (3) Guidelines for curricula, instructional materials, equipment, and the
24 organization, administration, and supervision of the program, including accounting,
25 auditing, and reporting procedures;
26 (4) MINIMUM FUNCTIONAL AND TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS TO
27 ENSURE OPTIMAL PERFORMANCE OF THE STATE’S ONLINE SPECIAL EDUCATION
28 SYSTEM, INCLUDING THE MARYLAND ONLINE INDIVIDUALIZED EDUCATION
29 PROGRAM AND THE MARYLAND ONLINE INDIVIDUALIZED FAMILY SERVICE PLAN;
30 [(4)] (5) Provisions for local, regional, and State day and residential
31 centers for children with disabilities who cannot be served appropriately in the public
32 schools;
33 [(5)] (6) Coordination of these special education services with services
34 given by any other government agency; and
35 [(6)] (7) Guidelines for approval of placement in nonpublic schools or
36 facilities if appropriate public services are not available.

